    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the indigenous people of the Aleutian island chain and the Pribilof Islands. This group is distinguished from the Alutiiq or Sugpiaq culture, also known as 'Aleut,' from Kodiak Island, Prince William Sound, outer Kenai Peninsula, and parts of the Alaskan Peninsula. The people prefer the term 'Unangax̂' to refer to themselves.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
